-- 
Greece Needs to Be Isolated From Other Countries, Carstens Says

-- B y   N a c h a   C a t t a n
-- 
2011-10-18T19:22:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-18/greece-needs-to-be-isolated-from-other-countries-carstens-says.html
Eurozone countries should be
isolated from  Greece , which needs additional debt
renegotiations, Mexico’s central bank Governor Agustin Carstens
said.  This “protection circle” should help stop contamination
from Greece into other markets, Carstens said in an interview
with Mexico-City based Radio Formula today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nacha Cattan in Mexico City at 
 ncattan@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
